# ── Brazilian Options Market Database ───────────────────────────────────────────
st.markdown('<div class="section-label">Brazilian Options Market Database (B3)</div>', unsafe_allow_html=True)
st.markdown("""
<div class="card">
    <div class="card-body" style="line-height:1.85;">
        GPFin maintains a proprietary database of Brazilian equity and ETF options collected directly
        through MetaTrader 5 integration and complementary market data sources. The database stores
        option-level information throughout the trading day, including bid/ask quotes, transaction prices,
        traded volume, implied volatility, Greeks, moneyness measures, and contract characteristics
        such as strike price, expiration date, and underlying asset.<br><br>
        The infrastructure supports the reconstruction of implied volatility surfaces, calibration of
        <strong>SVI models</strong>, estimation of variance risk premia, analysis of option market
        microstructure, and the development of systematic trading strategies. Historical datasets are
        organized in a structured <strong>SQL environment</strong> and integrated with Python-based
        research pipelines for data cleaning, feature engineering, backtesting, and empirical asset
        pricing applications.<br><br>
        The database currently serves as the foundation for research on
        <strong>implied volatility dynamics</strong>, straddle profitability, volatility risk premia,
        volatility scaling, and quantitative investment strategies in the Brazilian market.
    </div>
</div>
""", unsafe_allow_html=True)

